2005}) 22... Nd4 23. Be3 $14 {[%cal Gh2f3,Gh2g4] 1-0 (51) Demchenko,A (2679)
-Priasmoro,N (2449) Surakarta 2018. White should have better chances. The game
could continue like this:} h5 24. Nf3 Nxf3 25. Rxf3 b6 26. Kf1 $14 {[%cal
Gf1e2,Ga2a4,Ga4a5]}) 11. Ne2 $5 {or 11.Nh2 and then 12.Nd2, preparing f2-f4
push.} (11. Bh6 {As the practice proves, it gives nothing for White.} f6 12.
Bxg7 Qxg7 {and the problem is that Black hasn't yet short castled, which gives
him an opportunity to launch a kingside attack and flee with his king to the
queenside instead.} 13. a3 g5 $1 14. b4 g4 (14... h5 $5) 15. hxg4 Bxg4 16. Nh4
Ng6 17. Nxg6 hxg6 18. f3 Be6 $11 {1/2-1/2 (47) Reinderman,D (2561)-Hendriks,W 
(2373) Wijk aan Zee 2000}) 11... Ne6 12. Nh2 O-O 13. Rae1 b6 14. b3 a5 15. a4 {
[%cal Ge3h6,Gf2f4] and White can hope to outplay Black is the long run - the
plan remains the same. The position is about equal.}) 8. O-O {if you opt for
the short castle, I suggest to do it immediately without the inclusion of Be3
as Black won't manage to play e7-e5 and Nh5 in time to stop the f2-f4
advancement.} (8. Bf4 $5 {The alternative you can consider - it's the main
purpose is to stop Black from playing e7-e5 and to lure out the knight on h5
so that after a long castle White's attack gains one more tempo with g2-g4.}
Nh5 {certainly not the only move but I'll illustrate the idea.} 9. Be3 Qd6 10.
Qd2 e5 11. O-O-O b5 (11... Be6 $6 {the bishop appears to be misplaced on e6!
You will soon understand why.} 12. Kb1 b5 (12... a5 $2 13. Na4 $1) 13. Ne2 {
[%cal Gd2c3]} b4 14. g4 Nf6 15. Ng3 a5 16. Nf5 $1 {with the bishop on c8 this
idea would not be possible.} Bxf5 (16... gxf5 17. gxf5 Bd7 $2 18. Rhg1 Kh8 19.
Rxg7 Kxg7 20. Bxc5 $1 $18 {[%cal Gd2g5,Gd1g1]}) 17. gxf5 a4 18. Qe2 a3 19. b3 {
[%csl Rc5][%cal Gf3d2,Gh3h5] and White can combine a positional play with
attacking perspectives at the kingside}) (11... a5 $2 12. Na4 {[%csl Rc5,Rh5]})
(11... Nf4 $5 {[%cal Rf4e6]} 12. Bxf4 exf4 13. e5 $1 Bxe5 14. Nxe5 Qxe5 15.
Rde1 Qd6 (15... Qd4 16. Re4 Qd6 17. Rxf4 f5 18. Rf3 {[%cal Gd2h6]} Be6 19. Qh6
{[%cal Gh3h4,Gh4h5,Gf3g3]}) 16. Ne4 Qe5 17. h4 h5 18. g3 fxg3 19. Nxg3 $40 {
[%csl Rg8]}) 12. Ne2 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Gd2c3,Gd2a5]} b4 13. g4 Nf6 (13... Nf4
14. Nxf4 exf4 15. Bxf4 Qf6 16. e5 Qe6 17. Kb1 f5 18. Qe3 Qf7 19. Ng5 Qd5 20.
gxf5 Bxf5 21. Rhe1 $14) (13... Qf6 $2 {[%csl Rc5]} 14. gxh5 Qxf3 15. h6 Bf6 16.
Bxc5 $16) 14. Bh6 {[%cal Gf3d2,Gd2g5,Gd2c4] the purpose of the exchange is not
