19. Re4 (19. Rxe6 $6 {1/2-1/2 (57) Amin,B (2680)-Erdos,V (2628) Tbilisi 2017})
19... Rad8 20. Qe2 $14 {[%cal Ga1e1,Ge4e6]}) 9... cxd4 10. Qxd4 {[%cal Gd4h4,
Gb1c3,Gc1h6] in most of the occasions it is risky for Black to go for an
immediate short castle as White develops a dangerous initiative and Black will
be forced to play f7-f6 which weakens many squares in Black's camp.} Ne6 (10...
O-O 11. Qh4 f6 12. exf6 exf6 13. Bd2 $5 Ne6 14. Bc3 g5 15. Qe4 d5 16. cxd5 cxd5
