{[#]Black has just played 8...b4 with an idea to push back the white knight
and gain some tempos by attacking the pawn on e4. What did Black miss?} 9. Nd5
$1 {a classical motif in the Sicilian defense - White sacrifices a knight to
get to the black king. Black doesn't have a great choice - the knight on d5
doesn't allow Black to continue the development at the kingside.} exd5 10. exd5
Qc5 11. Re1+ Kd8 12. Qxc5 $1 Bxc5 13. Ne5 {[%cal Ge5f7] there's no way to
defend against the fork.} Kc7 14. Nxf7 Bb7 15. Nxh8 Rf8 16. Be3 Bxe3 17. Rxe3
Nf6 18. Re7 Rxh8 19. Rxg7 $16 {with excellent winning chances for White - the
pawns at the kingside are going to march forward sooner or later.} *

